          "INC-SPECT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The deuteron beam, at energies of 14 and 16 MeV, was",
                "pulsed and bunched to produce a pulse on target every",
                "512 ns, with a time width <4 ns and an average",
                "intensity of ~1 nA."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SCIN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Neutron spectra were measured using a 4.7-cm",
                "diam x 4.6-cm-long cylindrical NE-213 liquid",
                "scintillator mounted on a 5-cm (2-in.)-diam RCA-8850",
                "photomultiplier tube."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The target assembly consisted of a 1.9-cm-diam X",
                "6.4-mm-thick beryllium disk with a brass backing",
                "plate 1.6 mm thick."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TOF",
                "PSD"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The differential neutron spectra were",
                "measured using the TOF technique. The TOF spectra",
                "were recorded at flight paths of 1 and 3 m for times",
                "up to three days. The flight path measured 3.7 m.",
                "Several spectra were also obtained using a flight",
                "path of 2.0 m to check the data analysis and to",
                "obtain data for lower energy neutrons. Pulse-shape",
                "discrimination was used to suppress the gamma",
                "background, which measured <1% of the neutron flux."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "DATA-ERR",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": 10.0,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The present study allows us to select",
                "a consistent set of foil reactions that can be used",
                "to unfold neutron spectra in the energy range up to",
                "20 MeV with integral errors of <10%."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Scattering corrections were found to be insignificant,",
                "as might be expected due to the large size of the",
                "target room and the very forward peaked angular",
                "distribution of the emitted neutrons. Dead-time",
                "corrections, determined by gating the integrator",
                "frequency signal by the busy signal from the",
                "analog-to-digital converter, were <10%."
              ]
            }
          ],
